event.content:
The Montecito Motor Classic is a special Southern California car show.  And that’s due to a couple of reasons.  First, because it benefits area police organizations.  Moreover, because it’s a free family-friendly event that attracts some truly exquisite, and priceless, automobiles within the beautiful Polo grounds.

And this year’s event theme appears to be the concept car.  So, if incredible cars aren’t enough.  Adding concept vehicles to the mix makes the event a must-attend – in my book anyway.

Plus event benefits both the Santa Barbara Police Activities League and the Santa Barbara Police Foundation.

Priceless vehicles displayed

Montecito Motor Classic

Date: Sunday, October 10th, 2021
Location: Santa Barbara Polo And Racquet Club
Starts: 9 AM
Ends: 3 PM
Admission: Free
Vehicle Registration: HERE.

*Also, please note: iDriveSoCal does not host this event.  So if you’d like to learn more about the event please contact Montecito Motor Classic event organizers.  And that includes more specific details about attending, displaying your vehicle, and becoming a vendor or sponsor.

Additionally, for more of the best Southern California automotive events click HERE.

Plus, if you have an event that you think we should post?  Contact us HERE.
